#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:1
msgid "Style guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:3
msgid ""
"This document outlines the guidelines we use when writing documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:5
msgid "Writing style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:7
msgid "Aim for clarity and brevity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:9
msgid "I would have written a shorter letter, but I did not have the time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:11
msgid ""
"— [Blaise Pascal](https://en.m.wikiquote.org/w/index.php?"
"title=Blaise_Pascal&oldid=2978584#Quotes)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:13
msgid ""
"Readers' time and attention are limited. Take the time to be extraordinarily "
"respectful of their cognitive resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:16
msgid ""
"The same holds for communication directed to contributors and maintainers: "
"This is a public project, and many people will read what you write. Use this "
"leverage with care."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:20
msgid ""
"Follow the evidence-based [plain language guidelines](https://www."
"plainlanguage.gov/guidelines/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:22
msgid ""
"Don't use jargon. Readers may not be familiar with particular technical "
"terms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:23
msgid ""
"Don't use long, complicated words if there are shorter, simpler words that "
"convey the same meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:25
msgid "Use the imperative voice when giving instructions. For example, write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:28
msgid "Add the `python310` package to `buildInputs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:30
msgid ""
"Don't use a conversational tone, as it distracts from the content. For "
"example, don't write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:33
msgid ""
"Going forward, let's now add the `python310` package to `buildInputs` as we "
"have seen in the previous tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:35
msgid "Use inclusive language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:37
msgid ""
"Adapted from [Contributor Covenant] and [The Carpentries Code of Conduct]:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:39
msgid "Use welcoming and inclusive language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:40
msgid "Show empathy and respect towards other people"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:41
msgid "Be respectful of different viewpoints and experiences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:42
msgid "Give and gracefully accept constructive criticism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:43
msgid "Focus on what is best for the community"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:45
msgid ""
"Avoid idioms as they can be hard to understand for non-native English "
"speakers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:47
msgid ""
"Don't try to be funny. Humor is highly culturally sensitive. At best, jokes "
"may obfuscate the relevant instructions. At worst, jokes may offend readers "
"and invalidate our effort to help them learn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:52
msgid ""
"Don't use references to popular culture. What you may consider well-known "
"may be entirely obscure and distracting to people from different backgrounds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:58
msgid "Voice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:60
msgid ""
"Describe the subject factually and use the imperative voice in direct "
"instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:62
msgid ""
"Do not assume a personal relationship with readers, prefer clarity and "
"brevity to emotional appeal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:64
msgid ""
"Use \"you\" to refer to the reader and only use \"we\" to refer to the "
"authors. Both should be rarely needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:67
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:69
msgid ""
"You will have to deploy secrets to the remote machine. We chose to show the "
"explicit, manual process using `scp` here, but there are various tools to "
"automate that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:72
msgid "Be correct, cite sources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:74
msgid ""
"The only thing worse than no documentation is _incorrect documentation_. One "
"way to ensure correctness is by citing your sources. If you make a claim "
"about how something works (e.g. that a command line argument exists), link "
"to official documentation for that subject. We would like to maintain a "
"network of documentation, so linking to other documentation helps to "
"reinforce the documentation ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:79
msgid ""
"It is explicitly encouraged to update or restructure the manuals where "
"appropriate, to improve the overall experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:81
msgid "Markup and source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:83
msgid "Code samples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:85
msgid ""
"Always motivate code before showing it, describing in words what it is for "
"or what it will do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:87
msgid "Counter-example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:90
msgid ""
"Run this command:\n"
"\n"
"```bash\n"
":(){ :|:& };:\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:99
msgid ""
"Non-trivial examples may need additional explanation, especially if they use "
"concepts from outside the given context. Use a collapsed content box for "
"explanation that would distract from the reading flow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:102
#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:159
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:105
msgid ""
"Set off a [fork bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fork_bomb):\n"
"\n"
"```bash\n"
":(){ :|:& };:\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
":::{dropdown} Detailed explanation\n"
"This Bash command defines and executes a function `:` that recursively "
"spawns copies of itself, quickly consuming system resources.\n"
":::\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:118
msgid ""
"Always explain code in the text itself. Use comments in code samples very "
"sparingly, for instance to highlight a particular aspect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:121
msgid ""
"Readers tend to glance over large amounts of code when scanning for "
"information, even if most of it is comments. Especially beginners will "
"likely find reading more complex-looking code strenuous and may therefore "
"avoid it altogether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:124
msgid ""
"If a code sample appears to require a lot of inline explanation, consider "
"replacing it with a simpler one. If that's not possible, break the example "
"down into multiple parts, explain them separately, and then show the "
"combined result at the end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:127
msgid "Code samples that are _intended_ to work should work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:129
msgid ""
"If you are going to present an example that does not work (e.g. you're "
"illustrating a common mistake) explain this beforehand. Many readers will "
"get stuck trying to make example code work without reading ahead to find out "
"that the code isn't intended to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:132
msgid ""
"Code samples should all include a programming language when applicable for "
"syntax highlighting when rendered, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:134
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"print(\"Hello, World!\")\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:140
msgid "Headers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:142
msgid "Reserve the largest header (`#`) for the title."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:144
msgid ""
"Use Markdown headers `##` through `###` to divide up content in the body of "
"the document. Finer-grained headings are not necessarily better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:147
msgid "One line per sentence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:149
msgid "Write one sentence per line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:151
msgid ""
"This makes long sentences immediately visible. It also makes it easier to "
"review changes and provide direct suggestions, since the GitHub review "
"interface is line-oriented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:154
msgid "Links"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:156
msgid ""
"Use [reference links](https://github.github.com/gfm/#reference-link) – "
"sparingly – to ease source readability. Put definitions close to their first "
"use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:162
msgid ""
"We follow the [Diátaxis](https://diataxis.fr/) approach to structure "
"documentation.\n"
"This framework distinguishes between [tutorials], [guides], [reference], and "
"[explanation].\n"
"\n"
"[tutorials]: https://diataxis.fr/tutorials/\n"
"[guides]: https://diataxis.fr/how-to-guides/\n"
"[reference]: https://diataxis.fr/reference/\n"
"[explanation]: https://diataxis.fr/explanation/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:173
msgid ""
"Unless explicitly required to point to the latest version of an external "
"resource, all references should be [permanent links](https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Permalink)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:175
msgid "Many web services offer permalinks, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:177
msgid ""
"[GitHub URLs to specific commits](https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/"
"working-with-files/using-files/getting-permanent-links-to-files)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:178
msgid ""
"[Wikipedia URLs to specific page versions](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Wikipedia:Linking_to_Wikipedia#Permanent_links_to_old_versions_of_pages)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/style-guide.md:179
msgid ""
"[Internet Archive \"Save Page Now\" for persisting web pages](https://web."
"archive.org/save)"
msgstr ""
